column2: The lands that formed the [d_lindsey.GetFullName] have been reconquered from the Anglo-Saxons that once claimed the region for themselves.\n\nFrom this day on, the provinces around the former provincial capital of Lindum will once again belong 'de jure' to the Principality of Linnius and to the kingdom of Elmet. Any previous claim or birthright from the former Germanic rulers will no longer be recognized.

The coastal Saxon kingdom of South Seaxe has disappeared into the shadows of history.
